===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To remove [[obstruction]]s or [[impediment]]s.
#:* '''Clear''' the way.
# {{transitive}} To eliminate ambiguity or doubt form a matter; to [[clarify]]; especially, to [[clear up]].
# {{transitive}} To remove from [[suspicion]]; especially of having committed a crime
#:* The court '''cleared''' the man of murder.
# {{transitive}} To pass without interference; to [[miss]].
#:* The door just barely '''clears''' the table as it closes.
# {{intransitive}} To become clear.
#:* After a heavy rain, the sky '''cleared''' nicely for the evening.
# {{intransitive}} Of a [[check]] or financial [[transaction]], to go through as [[payment]]; to be [[process]]ed so that the money is transferred.
#:* The check might not '''clear''' for a couple of days.

